Captain Merlobo shipped these in on a few of his trips. My favorites are the Arabians.  ::Justine leaned on the fence and watched the horses romp around within.::  I love riding but don't get to do as much as I would like. We have some wild horses too but we let them stay wild.  Some things are just not meant to be penned.     <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fbe5b4><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/uhippolyte.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Hippolyte</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://hometown.aol.com/queenhippolyte/BC.html BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Queen</span><br>   <font color=#993300>(8/23/00 4:47 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://facelink.com/Hippolyte?flezbwidth=60&flezbheight=60 WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Horses of Skye</span><hr size=1> :::Hipp's brown eyes danced around looking from horse to horse.  She scanned them, their height, grace, form, muscle ton on some.  And then looked to Justine.:: Your arabians...the body is short oh them. ::she leans against the fence..and then suddenly a mare running along a fence caught her eye.  She was a pale fawn colour.  The mare held her head high as she began to slow to a canter..throwing her nose up and flairing her nostrils from time to time.  Hippolyte's eyes widened..as she watched the magnificent mare.  She wanted that mare so bad she hungered with the desire.  Keeping her eyes upon the mare who now turned and darted thru a grazing pair..scattering them.:: How much for that one...::she pointed:: the the tawny one...::then she turned her eyes to Justine :: parakalo....tell me..she is surely for sale?! <p>@xxx}}::::::::::::::::::::></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#fed995><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ujustineash.showPublicProfile?language=EN>JustineAsh</A></span><br